---
import DocsLayout from '../../../../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import Callout from '../../../../../components/Callout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout title="Remaining tickets" description="Work through Tickets 3–7 with verification guidance per ticket.">
  <h1 class="mb-6">Remaining Tickets</h1>
  <p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">You know the loop now: direct → verify → review → merge. Work through Tickets 3–7 using the same cycle. For each ticket, tell Claude to start it, then focus your verification on the areas below.</p>
  <p class="text-text-secondary mb-8">The key difference from Ticket 2: you're now verifying <em>visual</em> output against the design spec, not just checking that commands run.</p>

  <!-- Ticket 3 -->
  <div class="border border-border rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
    <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-1">Ticket 3: Site Layout & Navigation</h2>
    <p class="text-xs text-text-muted mb-4">frontend · Size M · Depends on T2</p>
    <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mb-3"><strong>Your verification focus:</strong></p>
    <ul class="text-sm text-text-secondary list-disc list-inside space-y-2 mb-3">
      <li><strong class="text-text">Header:</strong> Does it look right? Open DevTools (F12) → check font-family is Inter, font-size matches the design spec, colours match the hex values</li>
      <li><strong class="text-text">Sticky:</strong> Scroll down — does the header stay at the top?</li>
      <li><strong class="text-text">Mobile:</strong> DevTools → toggle device toolbar (Ctrl+Shift+M) → select iPhone SE. Does the nav become a hamburger? Does it open and close?</li>
      <li><strong class="text-text">Navigation:</strong> Click each nav link — does it smooth-scroll to the right section?</li>
      <li><strong class="text-text">Footer:</strong> Scroll to bottom — copyright year and contact info present?</li>
    </ul>
    <Callout variant="info">
      <p class="text-sm"><strong>DevTools tip:</strong> Right-click any element → Inspect. The Styles panel shows CSS properties. The Computed panel shows final calculated values (useful when Tailwind classes are confusing). The box model diagram shows margin and padding.</p>
    </Callout>
  </div>

  <!-- Ticket 4 -->
  <div class="border border-border rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
    <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-1">Ticket 4: Hero & Services</h2>
    <p class="text-xs text-text-muted mb-4">frontend · Size M · Depends on T3</p>
    <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mb-3"><strong>Your verification focus:</strong></p>
    <ul class="text-sm text-text-secondary list-disc list-inside space-y-2">
      <li><strong class="text-text">Hero:</strong> Is the background colour/gradient correct per the design spec? Is the CTA button visible and clickable?</li>
      <li><strong class="text-text">CTA:</strong> Click "Get in Touch" — does it scroll to the Contact section?</li>
      <li><strong class="text-text">Service cards:</strong> Count them. Exactly 6? Each with an icon area, name, and description?</li>
      <li><strong class="text-text">Responsive grid:</strong> Resize the viewport — 1 column on mobile, 2 on tablet, 3 on desktop?</li>
      <li><strong class="text-text">Content source:</strong> Open <code class="bg-bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-xs font-mono">src/data/content.js</code> — is all text coming from there, not hardcoded in components?</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <!-- Ticket 5 -->
  <div class="border border-border rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
    <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-1">Ticket 5: Testimonials & About</h2>
    <p class="text-xs text-text-muted mb-4">frontend · Size M · Depends on T4</p>
    <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mb-3"><strong>Your verification focus:</strong></p>
    <ul class="text-sm text-text-secondary list-disc list-inside space-y-2">
      <li><strong class="text-text">Testimonials:</strong> Exactly 4? Each with quote in quotation marks, name, suburb, and star rating?</li>
      <li><strong class="text-text">Star ratings:</strong> Are they visual (stars/icons), not text like "5/5"? Check the colour matches the design spec gold (#8B6914)</li>
      <li><strong class="text-text">Visual distinction:</strong> Do testimonials look different from other sections? (Different background, card style, or left border)</li>
      <li><strong class="text-text">About text:</strong> Is it readable? Check max-width in DevTools — should be around 600–700px, not stretching full width on desktop</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <!-- Ticket 6 -->
  <div class="border border-border rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
    <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-1">Ticket 6: Service Area & Contact</h2>
    <p class="text-xs text-text-muted mb-4">frontend · Size M · Depends on T5</p>
    <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mb-3"><strong>Your verification focus:</strong></p>
    <ul class="text-sm text-text-secondary list-disc list-inside space-y-2 mb-4">
      <li><strong class="text-text">Suburbs:</strong> Count them — all 10 from the PRD?</li>
      <li><strong class="text-text">Phone link:</strong> Inspect the phone number — is it an <code class="bg-bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-xs font-mono">&lt;a href="tel:..."&gt;</code>? Test on your actual phone if possible</li>
      <li><strong class="text-text">Email link:</strong> Is it a <code class="bg-bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-xs font-mono">mailto:</code> link?</li>
      <li><strong class="text-text">Business hours:</strong> Clearly formatted?</li>
    </ul>
    <Callout variant="warning">
      <p class="text-sm"><strong>Critical anti-scope check:</strong> Did Claude add a contact form? The PRD anti-scope explicitly says no forms — only phone and email links. If there's a form, direct Claude: "The PRD anti-scope says no contact form. Remove it and keep only the tel: and mailto: links." This is the most important catch in this project.</p>
    </Callout>
  </div>

  <!-- Ticket 7 -->
  <div class="border border-border rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
    <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-1">Ticket 7: SEO & Meta Tags</h2>
    <p class="text-xs text-text-muted mb-4">frontend · Size S · Depends on T6</p>
    <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mb-3"><strong>Your verification focus:</strong> This ticket's output is invisible — you can't see it by looking at the page. You need to check the source:</p>
    <ul class="text-sm text-text-secondary list-disc list-inside space-y-2">
      <li><strong class="text-text">Page title:</strong> Check the browser tab — contains "GreenScape Landscaping" and "Melbourne"?</li>
      <li><strong class="text-text">Meta description:</strong> Right-click → View Page Source → Ctrl+F for <code class="bg-bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-xs font-mono">&lt;meta name="description"</code></li>
      <li><strong class="text-text">Open Graph:</strong> Search page source for <code class="bg-bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-xs font-mono">og:title</code> — should find og:title, og:description, og:image, og:url</li>
      <li><strong class="text-text">Single H1:</strong> In DevTools Console, run <code class="bg-bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-xs font-mono">document.querySelectorAll('h1').length</code> — should return 1</li>
      <li><strong class="text-text">Lighthouse:</strong> DevTools → Lighthouse tab → run audit. SEO score should be 90+</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <p class="text-text-secondary">All frontend tickets done. Next: <a href="/web-dev/projects/1/build/finishing">deploy and finish the project</a>.</p>
</DocsLayout>
